# 🧠 Recall

> AI-powered command assistant for developers. Never forget a CLI command again.

---

## What it does

Recall helps you find and remember CLI commands using plain English. Powered by Claude AI.

```bash
# Don't remember the git command? Just ask:
recall ask "squash last 3 commits"
→ git rebase -i HEAD~3

# Found a command online and don't understand it?
recall explain "docker run -it --rm -v $(pwd):/app ubuntu bash"

# Save commands you use often:
recall save "git stash pop" --desc "restore last stash" --tags git,stash

# Search your personal library:
recall search "stash"
```

---

## Installation

```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/recall.git
cd recall

# Install
pip install -e .

# Set your Anthropic API key
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_key_here
```

---

## Commands

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `recall ask "<query>"` | Convert natural language to a command |
| `recall explain "<command>"` | Understand what a command does |
| `recall save "<command>"` | Save a command to your library |
| `recall search "<query>"` | Search your saved commands |
| `recall list` | List all saved commands |
| `recall list --tool git` | Filter by tool |
| `recall delete <id>` | Delete a saved command |

---

## Options

| Flag | Description |
|---|---|
| `--save` / `-s` | Auto-save the result after `ask` or `explain` |
| `--tool` | Filter list by tool name (git, docker, azure...) |
| `--yes` / `-y` | Skip confirmation prompts |

---

## Data

All your saved commands are stored locally in `~/.recall/recall.db` (SQLite).

